## Priority Order

When you're testing after building, run them in this order:

**First** — TC1, TC2, TC3, TC5 (schema). If these fail nothing else matters.

**Second** — TC13, TC14, TC19, TC21, TC24 (behavior probes). These are binary pass/fail and easy to check.

**Third** — TC16, TC17, TC18, TC22 (refine + compare). These test the hardest agent logic.

**Fourth** — TC6 through TC12 (recall quality). These tell you how good your retrieval is.

